Text.Value: Ah, but thanks to your little interference with our business, you are invested.
I'm not giving you a single gold piece.
Can you get me into the city proper?
Smart decision, sweetheart.

EditorData.NodeContext: Patronising - like telling a dog it's been good

Text.Value: Do you think you're clever coming in and undercutting us, sweetheart?

EditorData.logicalname: Greeting (Agreed to chase out for a half price)

Text.Value: That... was a mistake on your part, sweetie. A mistake the Guild will hear about.
Sweet of you to ask, but I don't think you can afford me.
I'll pay you, but I need some time to get the gold together.
Works for me. And, as we're all friends now, maybe I could get some Guild assistance of my own at some point?
I see you're a charitable sort - perhaps you have some benevolence to spare for us poor souls?

EditorData.logicalname: Greeting (Agreed to chase out for free)

Text.Value: I don't think so.
Do you think I was born yesterday? That's nowhere near Guild rates - half it and we'll call it a deal.
You can deal with those refugees yourself if you really want - I'm not invested.
Give me what you owe or maybe I'll just have to help myself to it when you're dead.
I'm not paying you that much - that's pure extortion.
I'd say 'you'll live to regret it' but honestly I'm not so sure you'd live.

EditorData.NodeContext: Clearly confident in her ability to kill the player

Text.Value: We were about to make a bit of extra cash before you butted in - you owe the Guild a cut.
Let's find out, shall we?
Real shame, that - but you'll have to find your charitable donation elsewhere.
Come on, boys - we've got places to be.
How presumptuous - it's almost endearin'. That'd be up to Nine-Fingers to decide.
I had a look in your employer's basement - did you know he puts explosives in children's toys?
You've stepped on the Guild's toes - and we'd like a little something to make it better.
Whatever you've been paid isn't worth dying to me - I know how to make it hurt.
And we can't have our mutual friend Arfur thinking he outsmarted us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost laughing through her quiet anger

Text.Value: Over my dead body.
I fought and killed an avatar of Myrkul recently. I think I can handle you.
I am the child of Lord Bhaal, this filthy city's eternal terror. Do you have any last words?

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChristianD] PLYR punches Zenovia in the face. Potential construction reuse > HUM_M_Rig_DFLT_CINE_ThrowPunch_StandL_03
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player swings at Zenovia and punches her (punch can be cut around to avoid showing actual contact)

Text.Value: Suppose I agree - what is this cut exactly?
Nine-Fingers herself?

EditorData.NodeContext: Amused and almost a little impressed at the audacity of the request

Text.Value: I am the child of Lord Bhaal, this filthy city's eternal terror. Do you have any last words?
I fought and killed an avatar of Myrkul recently. Do you have any last words?
As far as you're concerned, I am the Guild. And you know what? The price has just doubled. What a shame.
She's at the Guildhall in the Lower City - you can't miss her.
I'll almost feel sorry grinding you into the dirt.

EditorData.NodeContext: Amused; she definitely does not feel sorry for the player

Text.Value: You know, it's shocking how many people opt for the hard way when the easy way's right there. Any last words?

EditorData.NodeContext: Weary; was hoping this would be easier

Text.Value: It certainly could be - I'll be sure to let Nine-Fingers know you're interested in collaboratin'.
And I'm the Duke's personal bed warmer. I don't care what pies he's got his grimy little fingers in - just give me the gold.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sarcastic/starting to lose her patience ever so slightly

Text.Value: Or what?
Nothing for now - I just wanted to make sure it was an option.
Is the little dog trying to intimidate us? If it continues to bark, I will snap its neck.
Sharp little creature, aren't you? All right then - half.
I've always been a difficult person - I just can't help it.
Fine, here's your gold. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
Not my personal area of expertise - but Nine-Fingers'll know how.
Smooth talker, aren't you? What did you have in mind?
Well, boys - we did what we were paid for. Let's leave this lot to their misery.

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost sighing; it's been a long day

Text.Value: You're a clumsy little kitten, aren't you? Adorable.
You know, this was fun to begin with but now I'm getting bored.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChristianD] PLYR swings at Zenovia but she dodges it and kicks the player back. Considering a kick due to retargets
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player swings at Zenovia - who dodges out of the way and punches the player in return (punch can be cut around to avoid showing actual contact)

Text.Value: You think I'm just a pretty face? You'll pay up now - and just for trying it on, you can pay me double.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly playful - but most definitely a threat

Text.Value: Fine, here's your gold. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
*The Guild: a loose coalition uniting every criminal outfit in the city under one collective rule, from cutpurses to contract killers.*
I am the child of Lord Bhaal, this filthy city's eternal terror. Do you have any last words?
All right, I get it - how much do you want?
You know, somehow I can believe that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mild amusement - but she's still going to kill the player anyway

Text.Value: You're... serious. Let's forget this unpleasantness ever happened.
You think you can just waltz in here and meddle with our livelihood?
Then you're as much of a monster as he is.
I'm more of an 'actions' person.
Actually I've changed my mind - no deal.
Boys - how about a bit of the Rivington Rats' famous hospitality for our friend here?
You're full of crap.
Just a little something - consider it a gesture of good will. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost warm - maybe the player is going to appease her

Text.Value: I think you're overestimating your abilities somewhat - but I haven't got time for this.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to save face after successfully being intimidated; trying to pretend she's just too busy to deal with this and not afraid at the bloody threat

Text.Value: Calm down - how much are you after exactly?
I could do with a blade like yours - you ready for your next job?
Fine, here's your gold. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_3_01f129ea-b4dc-44b6-8154-9a948f876a82])
You took the words right out of my mouth.

EditorData.NodeContext: Relishing the imminent fight; she's glad to be able to kill the player (or try)

Text.Value: I respect your hustle, sweetheart, but it won't work on me.
Gold is nothing to me. My only pleasure in life is blood, and I'll be having yours.
I could give you that gold - but then I'd just take it back after I killed you.
I want to meet your boss.
We just lost a load of gold thanks to somebody interfering in our business, you see, and now we're a little out of pocket.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mock ignorance - and clearly slightly annoyed

Text.Value: Knock some sense into this upstart.
How much gold are we talking?

Synopsis: Zenovia Dawg, leader of the Rivington Rats, approaches the player after the refugee conflict at the merchant's house has been resolved - she doesn't take kindly to anyone interfering in her (or the Guild's) business.
